Are you building scripts for Call of Duty and do you want to create an universal, cross platform script 
that works for all button lay outs and that plays on Cold War, Modern Warfar & VanGuard? 
YES - YOU CAN! And this will get you going. I left some hints and instructions in here and also added
a user created function that leaves you with endless possibilties to create a razor sharp COD
script that players will love and celebrate. 

PREMIERING A SUPER COOL NEW FEATURE (FIRST SCRIPT WITH THIS UNIQUE FUNCTION EVER RELEASED): 
BUTTON CHECK AT START UP. This allows you to check if the script loaded your controller button configuartion 
("Default, Tactical, Bumper Jumper, etc etc") correctly. Thanks to Taylor and Batts I came to this idea. I based 
my cool function on their controller test script. The huge difference here is that my function actually reads the 
LABELS appointed to the controller button. So if you Press D-Pad Left in Cold War it will display "Ping." In any other
game it will display "Left." In Modern WF D-Pad Up = "Ping." In ColdWar "Up." The script displays all buttons for each
loadout correctly. And, you can still use the original labels next to the alternative labels. 
So, set_val (PING) and set_val (UP) or set_val (LEFT) -> will work as expected, 100% bug free. 
This is your SALVATION (if you are script writer and have been facing the PING button
issues due to different COD games you know what I am talking about). :D Hahaha. 

The Button Check runs at start-up of your script and switches off after 30 sec. A special thank you for TaylorDrift
who helped me in the right direction with the Button Check function. 

